value: Resident (presumably) in northern Nicaragua (single specimen from Peña Blanca, probably depto. Chontales); northern Costa Rica (Brasilia), and in South America east of the Andes from southeastern Colombia, eastern Ecuador, and Amazonian Brazil south to Paraguay and northeastern Argentina. A sight report for Panama (Canal area) requires confirmation.
Tropical Lowland Evergreen Forest, Secondary Forest, lowland pine savanna? (0-1350 m; Tropical Zone).
